    "observations": "The elimination constant and its variance were only described and not related to any covariates, leading to a simplistic description of the population that does not allow for individualised treatment, as can be seen from the results of “method A”, and requires samples to be measured to adjust for interindividual variability. The lack of covariates explains the lack in predictive power, resulting in a residual variance of Ke of >20% after the use of 4 samples",
